restaurant_description: We created a sophisticated, warm and harmonious setting to reflect the warmth of Indias hospitality when we opened this trend-setting restaurant in Magarpatta City in January 2013. We named our venture 'Global Punjab' to showcase the fusion between good quality food and world class service. Our passion for serving people is what drove us from the corporate world in the hospitality industry. After making a culinary mark on the heart of Magarpatta City, we spread our love for hospitality to Kharadi. Now in 2016. we add a jewel to the crown of our chain - Global Punjab, Nanded City, which is our biggest restaurant spread across 9000 sq ft. At Global Punjab, we offer you a wide range of dishes featuring exquisite spices and unusual ingredients prepared by our team of expert, dedicated chefs. Some signature dishes that have wowed our patrons are : Tangdi Mumtaz. Kalimiri Tangdi Kabab. Ajwaini Paneer, Veg. Patiala, Veg. Shabnami and Murg Mussallam. We aim at making dining at Global Punjab a wholesome experience in terms of the ambiance, service, entertainment and of course, delicious food! DJ Nights. Ghazal singers, private parties (Sublime Lounge at our outlet in Magarpatta). and live music are just some of the contributions towards this experience. We warmly invite you to take this culinary journey with us, to savor and discover new ingredients and dishes. We look forward to serving you again and again and again.

About Cherish Farm
Today, Cherish Farm is a 2 acre farmland on the banks of the tranquil Bhima River. The surroundings are serene and perfect for a quick weekend getaway. The farm house is surrounded by lush greenery and in fact if you can check out some fresh vegetables that we grow at our farm. These organic veggies are also be used to prepare a wholesome and nutritious meal for you! Cherish farm is perfect for group outings , family outings, Corporate Breakout Sessions, Meditation Retreats and for any special occasion !

restaurant_description: Located near Amanora Park Town, Sukoon Village is a beautiful and spacious restaurant. The restaurant has both indoor and outdoor seating with them. The indoor has used a lot of contemporary style furniture, bright colours with a mix of darker shades, which gives this place a dramatic effect. On the other hand, the outdoor seating comprises what someone might call an elevated form of patio furniture.  So you can swing along while digging into North Indian gravies and kebabs. If you're looking for a spot to dine with friends and have a big group, Sukoon has large tables, ideal for that. This also makes it a great spot for a family lunch on a Sunday.
